main event: The report includes observations of two unidentified objects, possibly a meteor, and their maneuvers. It also mentions the use of a theodolite by weather observers to track the objects' elevation and azimuth.
interesting points: The report documents the appearance of the unidentified objects in the theodolite of weather observers, detailing their elevation and azimuth.
Observations suggest that the first object disappeared while the second was heading south and then west.
The report mentions the involvement of a tower operator and provides details of altitude, direction, and speed of the observed objects.
The document is from a Project Blue Book report, which was a systematic study of UFOs conducted by the United States Air Force.
It is noted that no photograph was present in the report.
sighted object: two unidentified objects, possibly a meteor
witnesses: weather observers, tower operator, and ROKAF airman
